</center><p>
Source: "State Inmates, 1992-1994: Violent Offenders in State Prison: Sentences and Time Served," <i>Selected Findings</i>, Bureau of Justice Statistics, July 1995 
<p>
<b>3.</b>      Based on a 1991 survey of state prisoners, among <b>prisoners with a life sentence</b>:	<p><center>	69% said they expected to be released<br>		13% said they would never be released
</center><p>Source: <I> Ibid.</i><p><b>4.</b> Percent of Americans over <b>65</b> living on more than <b>$15,000 a year</b>:<p><center>		1990: 30%</center><p>Source: 1990 Census.<p><b>5.  Women in Labor force</b> (in Millions):<p>
<pre>
Year      Single       Married       Divorced/Widowed/Separated
1970	   7	      18.4	                5.9
1980	   11.2	      24.9	                8.8
1990	   14	      31	               11.2
</pre><p>Source: <i>Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994</i>. Table #626.<p>
