<center><img src="atr_logo.gif">
<h2>What's New</h2><p>
</center>
<b>Updated 7/5/96</b><P>
<ul>
<li>Thanks in part to the 1994 Republican takeover of Congress, 
Cost of Government Day came a few days earlier this year. Find out how many days per year you work for the government in
ATR's updated report on <a href="cogdpak.html">
Cost of Government Day 1996</a>.
<li>Citizens around the nation benefit from restrictions on the ability to raise their taxes.  Find out which states have <a href="/atr/superlim.html">Supermajority Tax Limitations.</a>
<li>Over 30 bills have been introduced nation-wide to enact supermajority protection against tax increases.  Find out <a href="/atr/supersta.html">which states</a> have taken such action in the past two years.
<li>ATR has compiled a list of those <a href="/atr/supercon.html">other articles in the Constitution</a> which require supermajority voting.  
<li>Find out if your elected officials have taken the <a href="/atr/pledge/">Taxpayer Protection Pledge.</a> 
</ul>
<P>
