<TITLE>Town Hall - The "Train Wreck Contest"</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg"> 
<center>
<h2>When Will Government Be Back in Business?</h2>

<hr size="4" width ="65%"><p>
</center>





After much talk and fanfare, the "<a href="/townhall/spotlights/9-18-95/welcome.html.cgi">train wreck</a>" is upon us and the Federal government has closed  (has anyone noticed?).  What that really means is that as of noon today (11/14/95), all nonessential services were stopped .  Which makes us ask, if some services are nonessential, why are taxpayers paying for them?<p> 

Never wanting to miss an opportunity to give away T-shirts to our users, weve' come up with a little contest.  When do you think the government will be reopened?  The rules are simple.  If you correctly guess the day and time at which the President signs the reconciliation bill, you will be eligible to win one of our fine shirts. 
<p>
The person who guesses correctly, or comes the closest, will be the winner.  If two or more get the day and time right, the recipient will be randomly selected from a pool made up of those who guessed correctly.  All submissions sent after the announcement of an agreement between the Congress and the President will not be eligible.  Remember, only one guess per person.
<p>
Let us know what you think about the closing of the Federal government.  Depending on ones political outlook, this is 
 either a disaster or a godsend.  One thing is sure, commuting into our Capitol Hill offices will be much easier as
long as this situation continues.
<p>


